## IV. VISTAS DE ARQUITECTURA (IEEE 1016)

### Vista de Datos (ERD Conceptual)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    FB_API_SETTINGS ||--o{ FB_FIELD_MAPPINGS : "configura"
    FB_API_SETTINGS ||--|| FB_SAVE_BUTTON : "define"
    FB_API_SETTINGS ||--o{ FB_RECORD_STATES : "genera"
    FB_FIELD_MAPPINGS ||--o{ FB_RECORD_STATES : "mapea"

    FB_API_SETTINGS {
        string url
        string method
        json headers
    }
    FB_FIELD_MAPPINGS {
        string json_key
        string dom_selector
        enum selector_type
    }
    FB_SAVE_BUTTON {
        string dom_selector
    }
    FB_RECORD_STATES {
        string record_id PK
        enum status
        int timestamp
    }
```

### Vista de Integración (Componentes MV3)

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Chrome Extension (MV3)"
        BG["background.js<br/>(Service Worker)"]
        SP["sidepanel.js<br/>(SidePanel UI)"]
        CS["content.js<br/>(Content Script)"]
        ST["chrome.storage.local"]
    end

    API["API REST Externa<br/>(configurable)"]
    DOM["DOM Formulario<br/>(abastible.cl)"]

    SP -- "chrome.runtime.sendMessage<br/>{action: 'fetchData'}" --> BG
    BG -- "fetch(url)" --> API
    API -- "JSON Response" --> BG
    BG -- "sendResponse(data)" --> SP

    SP -- "chrome.tabs.sendMessage<br/>{action: 'fillForm', data}" --> CS
    CS -- "Inyecta valores +<br/>dispara input/change/blur" --> DOM

    CS -- "chrome.runtime.sendMessage<br/>{action: 'markUsed', recordId}" --> BG
    BG -- "chrome.storage.local.set()" --> ST

    SP -- "chrome.storage.local.get()" --> ST

    CS -- "addEventListener('click')<br/>en save_button" --> DOM
```

### Vista de Endpoints API (Contrato de Datos)

| Tipo | Canal | Payload | Dirección |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fetchData` | `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` | `{ action: 'fetchData' }` | SidePanel → Background |
| `fetchData:response` | `sendResponse` | `{ success: boolean, data: object[] }` | Background → SidePanel |
| `fillForm` | `chrome.tabs.sendMessage` | `{ action: 'fillForm', record: object, mappings: object[] }` | SidePanel → Content |
| `startInspector` | `chrome.tabs.sendMessage` | `{ action: 'startInspector' }` | SidePanel → Content |
| `selectorCaptured` | `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` | `{ action: 'selectorCaptured', selector: string, type: string }` | Content → SidePanel |
| `markUsed` | `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` | `{ action: 'markUsed', recordId: string }` | Content → Background |

### Flujo de Valor (Input → Persistencia)

```
1. [Usuario] Configura URL API en SidePanel (Modo Setting)
       ↓
2. [background.js] Ejecuta sample fetch → devuelve llaves JSON
       ↓
3. [Usuario] Activa Inspector → selecciona campo en DOM
       ↓
4. [content.js] Captura selector CSS estable → envía a SidePanel
       ↓
5. [Usuario] Vincula selector con llave JSON → persiste en chrome.storage.local
       ↓
6. [Usuario] Cambia a Modo Uso → ve lista de registros (Pendientes/Utilizados)
       ↓
7. [Usuario] Presiona "Llenar Formulario" en un registro
       ↓
8. [content.js] Inyecta valores + dispara eventos (input, change, blur)
       ↓
9. [Usuario] Revisa datos y presiona botón de guardado (físicamente)
       ↓
10. [content.js] Detecta clic en save_button → notifica a background.js
       ↓
11. [background.js] Actualiza fb_record_states: status = 'used' en chrome.storage.local
```

